# Web Viz Plan Maintenance

For every feature or bug fix, add a new entry at the top of the plan document (below the frontmatter), not the bottom, using this format:

```markdown
## ✨ Feature #N | 🐛 Bug Fix #N

- 🎯 **Goal:** <what this change achieves>
- 📝 **Description:** <implementation details and approach>
- 🧪 **Test:** `<test command>` — <pass / fail + summary>
- 🔄 **Integration / Regression:** `<command>` — <pass / fail + summary>
```

### Field guidance

- **Python commands** — for this project, run any Python script via `uv run --project server python ...` (not `python ...`).

- **Test** — the exact command a developer would run to verify this specific feature works (e.g. `uv run --project server python scripts/run_camera.py`, `make test-client`, `npm test`). Use `N/A` only for pure documentation or config changes with nothing executable.
- **Integration / Regression** — the exact command to verify the feature does not break existing functionality. This should run the broadest relevant test suite or smoke-test (e.g. `make test-client`, `uv run --project server python scripts/run_camera.py`). If no integration test exists yet, still list the most relevant runnable command so a developer knows how to verify. Use `N/A` only when truly nothing is runnable.

Treat `.cursor/plans/web-viz.plan.md` as the source of truth for project work.
